§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The variation of a measure is the measure obtained by
    adding the positive and negative parts of the measure. ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $μ$ be a measure. ⦉

  ‖ We denote the variation of $μ$ by $\vmeas{μ}$. ⦉

⦉
